Homepage: http://www.tuxonice.net/userui

Package: tuxonice-userui
Architecture: i386 ia64 powerpc ppc64 amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: hibernate
Provides: suspend2-userui
Replaces: suspend2-userui (<< 0.7.2+clean-3)
Conflicts: suspend2-userui (<< 0.7.2+clean-3)
Description: user-space interfaces for TuxOnIce
 TuxOnIce is an alternative implementation to suspend a linux machine
 by writing its state to memory for later resuming. A kernel patch for
 TuxOnIce is available separately.
 .
 This package provides several user interfaces which improve the
 user's experience during the suspend and resume processes. It is not
 needed for TuxOnIce functionality.

Package: suspend2-userui
Depends: tuxonice-userui
Architecture: all
Description: transitional dummy package
 This package is provided to smooth upgrade to TuxOnIce, because
 suspend2-userui package has been renamed to tuxonice-userui. It can
 be safely removed after upgrade.
